cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper deals with facial expression recognition using machine learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The use of feature descriptors such as LBP-TOP, HOOF, and HOG 3D also suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper involves evaluating the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which could also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
